<subsection xml:id="subsec-expressing-numbers-in-standard-form">
    <title>Expressing Numbers in Standard Form</title>
    <p>
        <alert>Standard form</alert> is a way of representing numbers in a clear and consistent way. 
        A number expressed in the form of <m>p \times 10^n</m>,
        where <m>n</m> is an integer and <m>p</m> is greater than zero but less than <m>10 </m> is said to be in standard form.
    </p>
